abla_{\vec{k}}\omega(\vec{k})=  rac{1}{\hbar}
abla_{\vec{k}}E(\vec{k}) $$ 在一维情况下, 电子因为外力做功而获得能量 $\delta E$ $$ \delta E = F v_{g}\cdot\delta t\ \Rightarrow \delta E =  rac{\mathrm{d}E}{\mathrm{d}k}\cdot\delta k = \hbar v_{g}\cdot\delta k $$ 所以我们可以观察到一个类似于质量的参数在方程中产生作用: $$ \hbar rac{\mathrm{d}k}{\mathrm{d}t} = F(\hbar rac{\mathrm{d}\vec{k}}{\mathrm{d}t}=\vec{F})\  rac{\mathrm{d}v_{g}}{\mathrm{d}t} =  rac{1}{\hbar} rac{\mathrm{d}}{\mathrm{d}t}( rac{\mathrm{d}E}{\mathrm{d}k}) =  rac{1}{\hbar} rac{\mathrm{d}^{2}E}{\mathrm{d}k^2} rac{\mathrm{d}k}{\mathrm{d}t} =  rac{1}{\hbar^{2}} rac{\mathrm{d}^{2}E}{\mathrm{d}k^{2}}F =  rac{1}{m^{*}} $$ 所以我们就可以定义有效质量 $m^{*}$: $$  rac{1}{m^{*}} =  rac{1}{\hbar^{2}} rac{\mathrm{d}^2 E}{\mathrm{d}k^2} $$ 而针对某个特定方向时, 即有 $$ \left( rac{1}{m{*}}ight)_{\mu
u}= rac{1}{\hbar^{2}} rac{\mathrm{d}^{2}E}{\mathrm{d}k_{\mu}\mathrm{d}k_{
